Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and halve
@Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.
Zest and quarter @Lemon{1} (for 4, zest one lemon and quarter both).
Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, spread potatoes out across entire sheet.

Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the zucchini then).

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, toss zucchini with a drizzle of olive oil and a
pinch of salt and pepper.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven;
carefully add zucchini to empty side.

> For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add zucchini to a second sheet;
> roast on middle rack.

Return to top rack until potatoes are golden brown and zucchini is lightly
browned, ~{12-15%minutes} more.

Pat @Salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and
pepper.

Heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} and @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add salmon skin sides down and cook until skin is crisp and
fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook to desired
doneness, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Stir in @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1},
half the @Dijon Mustard{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), juice from half the
lemon, and @Water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup for 4). Simmer until slightly thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, half the chives, and @Butter{1%tablespoon}
(2 TBSP for 4).

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, add water 1 tsp at a time until it reaches a
> drizzling consistency.

Season with salt and pepper.

Toss zucchini with lemon zest.

Divide salmon, potato wedges, and zucchini between #plates{}. Drizzle sauce
over salmon. Garnish with remaining chives if desired. Serve with remaining
lemon wedges on the side.